## Why This Is Asked

Tests end-to-end KCA design across edge-to-cloud, including hardware-root attestation, regional bootstrap, central CA enrollment, and tenant-scoped TLS with short TTLs. It also probes crypto agility (PQC fallback), revocation/auditing, and practical testing of tenant migrations and data isolation under load.

## Key Concepts

- Edge TPM/TEE attestation and hardware roots
- Regional bootstrap and central KCA enrollment
- SPIFFE IDs and per-tenant scopes (edge-rt)
- Crypto agility with PQC fallback and TLS configuration
- Revocation handling, auditing, and policy binding

## Code Example

```javascript
// Pseudo steps for enrollment and attestation (not production-ready)
async function onboardEdgeNode(node, region, tenant) {
  const attestation = await TPM.attest(node, region);
  const csr = generateCSR(node.publicKey, tenantSPIFFE(tenant));
  const cert = await centralKCA.enroll(csr, { ttl: 120, scope: 'edge-rt' });
  node.install(cert, csr.privateKey);
  logAudit({ event: 'edge_onboard', tenant, region, ttl: 120 });
  return cert;
}
```

## Follow-up Questions

- How would you measure and optimize reattestation latency under burst edge load?
- How would you handle PQC negotiation failures and certificate revocation at scale?

